## Service Implementation Template

This template should be used to document the implementation details of a service before coding. 
Replace [ServiceName] with the actual service name (e.g., SupabaseAuth, AzureStt).

```
# [ServiceName] Service Implementation

## Purpose & Functionality
- [Describe what this service does and its role in the system]
- [List primary features and responsibilities]

## Dependencies
- **External Services:** [List any external APIs or services]
- **Internal Dependencies:** [List dependent internal modules/services]
- **Required Credentials:** [List required API keys or credentials]

## Data Models
- [List and describe relevant database models]
- [Include relationships between models]

## Implementation Details

### Core Components
- [List main classes/interfaces/functions to implement]
- [Describe file structure]

### Main Flows
1. [Detailed description of first process flow]
   - [Inputs]
   - [Step 1]
   - [Step 2]
   - [...]
   - [Outputs]

2. [Detailed description of second process flow]
   - [...]

### Error Handling
- [Common error cases and how to handle them]
- [Retry strategies]
- [Fallback mechanisms]

### Security Considerations
- [Security measures]
- [Credential handling]
- [Data protection]

## API Interface
```typescript
// Interface definition
interface I[ServiceName]Service {
  // Method signatures with documentation
  methodName(param1: Type, param2: Type): ReturnType;
}
```

## Integration Test Plan
- [Test scenarios]
- [Mock requirements]
- [Validation criteria]

## Future Enhancements
- [Planned features for future iterations]
- [Potential optimizations]
```

To use this template, create a new file in the `.cursor/rules/` directory with the name of your service, e.g., `.cursor/rules/supabase-auth.mdc`. Then fill in the template with the specific implementation details of that service.

